com.facebook.buck.java

Class DefaultJavaLibraryRule

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.facebook.buck.rules.AbstractCachingBuildRule
      • com.facebook.buck.java.DefaultJavaLibraryRule
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    HasClasspathEntries, HasJavaSrcs, JavaLibraryRule, AbiRule, BuildRule, Comparable<BuildRule>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AndroidLibraryRule, FakeDefaultJavaLibraryRule, JavaTestRule

    public class DefaultJavaLibraryRule
extends AbstractCachingBuildRule
implements JavaLibraryRule, AbiRule, HasJavaSrcs, HasClasspathEntries
    Suppose this were a rule defined in src/com/facebook/feed/BUILD: 
     java_library(
   name = 'feed',
   srcs = [
     'FeedStoryRenderer.java',
   ],
   deps = [
     '//src/com/facebook/feed/model:model',
     '//third-party/java/guava:guava',
   ],
 )
    Then this would compile FeedStoryRenderer.java against Guava and the classes generated from the //src/com/facebook/feed/model:model rule.

      • appendToRuleKey

        protected RuleKey.Builder appendToRuleKey(RuleKey.Builder builder)
        getRuleKey() and createRuleKeyWithoutDeps() uses this when constructing RuleKeys for this class. Every subclass that extends the rule state in a way that matters to idempotency must override appendToRuleKey(com.facebook.buck.rules.RuleKey.Builder) and append its state to the RuleKey.Builder returned by its superclass's appendToRuleKey(com.facebook.buck.rules.RuleKey.Builder) implementation. Example: 
         @Override
 protected RuleKey.Builder appendToRuleKey(RuleKey.Builder builder) {
   return super.appendToRuleKey(builder)
       .set("srcs", srcs),
       .set("resources", resources);
 }

        @Nullable
protected List<String> getInputsToCompareToOutput()
        Description copied from class: AbstractCachingBuildRule
        Get the set of input files whose contents should be hashed for the purpose of determining whether this rule is cached.

        Note that the collection of inputs is specified as a list, because for some build rules (such as Genrule), the order of the inputs is significant. If the order of the inputs is not significant for the build rule, then the list should be alphabetized so that lists with the same elements will be .equals() to one another.

      • initializeFromDisk

        public boolean initializeFromDisk(ProjectFilesystem projectFilesystem)
        Description copied from class: AbstractCachingBuildRule
        For a rule that is read from the build cache, it may have fields that would normally be populated by executing the steps returned by AbstractCachingBuildRule.buildInternal(BuildContext). Because AbstractCachingBuildRule.buildInternal(BuildContext) is not invoked for cached rules, a rule may need to implement this method to populate those fields in some other way. For a cached rule, this method will be invoked just before the future returned by AbstractCachingBuildRule.build(BuildContext) is resolved.

        By default, this method does nothing except return true.

        Specified by:

      • getAbiKey

        public Optional<Sha1HashCode> getAbiKey()
        Description copied from interface: JavaLibraryRule
        Returns a SHA-1 hash that represents the ABI for the Java files returned by JavaLibraryRule.getJavaSrcs(). If JavaLibraryRule.getJavaSrcs() returns an empty collection, then this will return a non-absent value. The only requirement on the hash is that equal hashes imply equal ABIs.

        Because the ABI is computed as part of the build process, this rule cannot be invoked until after this rule is built.

        Returns Optional.absent() if the rule did not build successfully, or if the ABI could not be extracted for any reason.

        Specified by:
        getAbiKey in interface JavaLibraryRule
